						<summary>

						<p>Slab set up in survey No. 200 to the east of the village.</p>						

						<p>AMBADĒVA.</p>						

						<p>1297 A.D.</p>						

						<p>It is dated Śaka 1219, Vijaya, Jyēshṭha, śu. 15, Thursday, corresponding to June 11, 1297 A.D. (cyclic year being the Hēmalamba).</p>						

						<p>Damaged and incomplete. It records the strings of titles like <hi rend="italic">Gaṇḍaragaṇḍa, Chalameṭṭugaṇḍa, Kāyastha kula kamala mārttāṇḍa etc.,</hi> of the Kāyastha general obviously Aṁbadēva.</p>						

						</summary>
